48. Record number handling in PHP with suitable examples.
<?php
echo "<h2>1. Record Numbering in a Simple Array</h2>";
$students = ["Alice", "Bob", "Charlie", "Diana"];
$recordNumber = 1;
foreach ($students as $student) {
    echo "Record $recordNumber: $student<br>";
    $recordNumber++;
}
echo "<h2>2. Record Numbering Using Array Index</h2>";
foreach ($students as $index => $student) {
    echo "Record " . ($index + 1) . ": $student<br>";
}
echo "<h2>3. Simulated Database Record Handling</h2>";
// Simulate database result set as an array of associative arrays
$results = [
    ["id" => 101, "name" => "John"],
    ["id" => 102, "name" => "Jane"],
    ["id" => 103, "name" => "Tom"]
];
$recordNumber = 1;
foreach ($results as $row) {
    echo "Record $recordNumber: ID = " . $row['id'] . ", Name = " . $row['name'] . "<br>";
    $recordNumber++;
}
echo "<h2>4. Record Numbering with Pagination</h2>";
// Simulate current page and records per page
$currentPage = 3;
$recordsPerPage = 5;
// Calculate starting record number
$startRecordNumber = ($currentPage - 1) * $recordsPerPage + 1;
// Simulated page data
$pageData = ["Record A", "Record B", "Record C", "Record D", "Record E"];

foreach ($pageData as $index => $value) {
    $recordNumber = $startRecordNumber + $index;
    echo "Record $recordNumber: $value<br>";
}
?>

OUTPUT
1. Record Numbering in a Simple Array
Record 1: Alice
Record 2: Bob
Record 3: Charlie
Record 4: Diana
2. Record Numbering Using Array Index
Record 1: Alice
Record 2: Bob
Record 3: Charlie
Record 4: Diana
3. Simulated Database Record Handling
Record 1: ID = 101, Name = John
Record 2: ID = 102, Name = Jane
Record 3: ID = 103, Name = Tom
4. Record Numbering with Pagination
Record 11: Record A
Record 12: Record B
Record 13: Record C
Record 14: Record D
Record 15: Record E
